%T A392330 538484,834615,1381950
%N A392330 a(n) is the number of 5 element sets of distinct integer-sided trapezoids whose base angles are 60 degrees of total area n^2 but which cannot fill an equilateral triangular grid of side n units.
%C A392330 These sets consist of distinct integer-sided trapezoids formed within the equilateral triangular grid of side n units such that the total area is n^2.
%C A392330 A trapezoid whose base angles are 60 degrees with larger base b and legs s is denoted by {b X s} here.
%e A392330 Sequence has 2 sets for n = 7:
%e A392330   {(3 X 1), (5 X 1), (3 X 2), (4 X 2), (4 X 3)},
%e A392330   {(2 X 1), (6 X 1), (3 X 2), (4 X 2), (4 X 3)}.
%e A392330 Therefore a(7) = 2.
%Y A392330 Cf. A389392, A389518, A390523, A391498, A391499, A393545, A393432.
